## <a id='roles'></a> Single Sign-On Roles

Single Sign-On for Pivotal Cloud Foundry utilizes existing user roles as well as a SSO-specific Plan Administrator role. These roles are allowed the following actions listed below.

<table border="1" class="nice">
  <tr><th>Actions</th><th>PCF Administrator</th><th>Plan Administrator</th><th>Space Developer</th></tr>
  <tr><th>Manage Service Plans</th><td>X</td><td></td><td></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Manage Identity Providers</th><td>X</td><td>X</td><td></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Manage Service Instances</th><td>X</td><td>X</td><td>X</span></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Manage Applications</th><td>X</td><td>X</td><td>X</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Manage Resources</th><td>X</td><td>X</td><td>X</td></tr>
</table>

Manage Service Plans - Access includes the create, edit and delete of service plans.

Manage Identity Providers - Access includes the management of the internal user store and its password policy. This also allows users to create and configure external identity providers for single sign-on.

Manage Service Instances - Access includes create, edit and delete of services instances. This also allows users to bind applications to a service instance to be associated with a plan.

Manage Applications - Access includes create, edit and delete of applications.

Manage Resources - Access includes create, edit and delete of resources and permissions.

<strong>For more detailed access and actions that user roles can have, please view the corresponding manage guides.</strong>

